{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775835746386,"sessionID":"ses_287f3c6b0ffeDZ0hfYvo2PU9oI","part":{"id":"prt_d780f0bb0001561ycQYEEPcuxk","messageID":"msg_d780f0662001uOb3LXM6vMMOkw","sessionID":"ses_287f3c6b0ffeDZ0hfYvo2PU9oI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_17db7b0da52144968f643dad","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/store\n4: **Language:** Go\n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## Problem\n8: \n9: AR-012 完成了 Session Store 的接口定义和基础实现，但当前 `pkg/store` 的实现与 Session Store spec/design 文档存在多处偏差，导致无法满足下游组件（Reconciler、GC、Router）的完整需求：\n10: \n11: 1. **接口签名不一致** — spec 定义 `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` 和 `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandboxStore *SandboxInfo)`，当前实现为 `GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` 和 `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID, info)`（sessionID 作为独立参数）\n12: 2. **错误消息不匹配** — spec 要求 `ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")`，当前实现为 `\"sandbox not found\"`\n13: 3. **List 方法性能不足** — spec 要求 `ListExpiredSandboxes`/`ListInactiveSandboxes` 使用 Pipeline/MGET 批量加载 sandbox 数据，当前实现使用循环逐个 GET（N+1 查询）\n14: 4. **缺少 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` 辅助方法** — spec 要求 Valkey 实现使用 MGET 批量加载，当前实现逐个 GET\n15: 5. **参数类型不一致** — spec 定义 `limit int64`，当前实现为 `limit int`\n16: 6. **StoreSandbox 缺少 ExpiresAt 零值校验** — spec 要求拒绝 `ExpiresAt` 为零的 sandbox\n17: \n18: 这些偏差会导致：下游组件按 spec 调用时编译失败；大规模 sandbox 场景下 List 查询性能退化；错误处理语义不统一。\n19: \n20: ## Proposed Solution\n21: \n22: 对齐当前实现与 Session Store spec/design 文档，具体修改：\n23: \n24: 1. **修正 Store 接口签名** — 将 `GetSandbox` 重命名为 `GetSandboxBySessionID`；将 `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID, info)` 改为 `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandboxStore *SandboxInfo)`（从 `SandboxInfo.SessionID` 提取 sessionID）\n25: 2. **修正 ErrNotFound 消息** — 改为 `\"store: not found\"`\n26: 3. **新增 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` 辅助方法** — Redis 使用 Pipeline GET，Valkey 使用 MGET 批量加载\n27: 4. **重构 List 方法** — 使用 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` 替代循环 GET\n28: 5. **修正参数类型** — `limit` 从 `int` 改为 `int64`\n29: 6. **增加 ExpiresAt 零值校验** — `StoreSandbox` 拒绝 `ExpiresAt.IsZero()` 的 sandbox\n30: \n31: ## Scope\n32: \n33: ### In Scope\n34: \n35: 1. **接口签名修正**（`store.go`）\n36:    - `GetSandbox` → `GetSandboxBySessionID`\n37:    - `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo)` → `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo)`\n38:    - `limit int` → `limit int64`（`ListExpiredSandboxes`、`ListInactiveSandboxes`）\n39: \n40: 2. **错误消息修正**（`store.go`）\n41:    - `ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")`\n42: \n43: 3. **Redis 实现对齐**（`store_redis.go`）\n44:    - 新增 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs []string)` 使用 Pipeline GET 批量加载\n45:    - `ListExpiredSandboxes`/`ListInactiveSandboxes` 调用 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs`\n46:    - `StoreSandbox` 增加 `ExpiresAt.IsZero()` 校验\n47:    - `StoreSandbox` 从 `info.SessionID` 提取 sessionID\n48: \n49: 4. **Valkey 实现对齐**（`store_valkey.go`）\n50:    - 新增 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs []string)` 使用 MGET 批量加载\n51:    - `ListExpiredSandboxes`/`ListInactiveSandboxes` 调用 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs`\n52:    - `StoreSandbox` 增加 `ExpiresAt.IsZero()` 校验\n53:    - `StoreSandbox` 从 `info.SessionID` 提取 sessionID\n54: \n55: 5. **单例初始化**（`singleton.go`）— 无变更（已符合 spec）\n56: \n57: 6. **编解码器**（`codec.go`）— 无变更（已符合 spec）\n58: \n59: 7. **测试更新**\n60:    - `store_redis_test.go` — 更新测试用例适配新接口签名\n61:    - `store_valkey_test.go` — 更新测试用例适配新接口签名\n62:    - `singleton_test.go` — 无变更\n63:    - `codec_test.go` — 无变更\n64: \n65: ### Out of Scope\n66: \n67: - `ListSandboxes` 方法的 spec 对齐（spec 中未定义此方法，保留现状）\n68: - Helm Chart 或部署配置变更\n69: - K8s CRD 或 client-go 变更\n70: - Router、Reconciler、GC 组件的调用方适配（由各自 AR 覆盖）\n71: - Valkey 集群模式 hash slot 问题（部署层面考虑，代码中添加注释说明）\n72: \n73: ## Dependencies\n74: \n75: | 依赖 | 状态 | 说明 |\n76: |------|------|------|\n77: | AR-012（会话存储接口定义） | 已完成 | 提供了基础接口和实现框架 |\n78: | `pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo` | 已存在 | 需确认 `SessionID` 字段可用 |\n79: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | 已引入 | Redis 客户端依赖 |\n80: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | 已引入 | Valkey 客户端依赖 |\n81: \n82: ## Risks & Mitigations\n83: \n84: | 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n85: |------|------|----------|\n86: | 接口签名变更导致调用方编译失败 | 高 | 本 AR 仅修改 store 包；调用方适配由各自 AR 同步跟进；提供迁移指南 |\n87: | Valkey MGET 跨 hash slot 失败（集群模式） | 中 | 在代码注释中说明 key 需落在同一 slot 的要求；建议使用 hash tag `{session}:{id}` |\n88: | `StoreSandbox` 从 `info.SessionID` 提取 sessionID 可能与调用方传入不一致 | 中 | 在方法文档中明确说明以 `info.SessionID` 为准；调用方需确保一致性 |\n89: | Pipeline/MGET 批量加载在大规模场景下内存占用增加 | 低 | `limit` 参数限制单次加载数量（默认 GC 调用时 limit 合理）；可后续优化为流式加载 |\n90: | `ExpiresAt.IsZero()` 校验可能拒绝合法的永不过期 sandbox | 低 | 当前 spec 明确要求 ExpiresAt 非零；如需支持永不过期，需 spec 变更 |\n\n(End of file - total 90 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n\n**Module:** pkg/store\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** M\n\n## Problem\n\nAR-012 完成了 Session Store 的接口定义和基础实现，但当前 `pkg/store` 的实现与 Session Store spec/design 文档存在多处偏差，导致无法满足下游组件（Reconciler、GC、Router）的完整需求：\n\n1. **接口签名不一致** — spec 定义 `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` 和 `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandboxStore *SandboxInfo)`，当前实现为 `GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` 和 `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID, info)`（sessionID 作为独立参数）\n2. **错误消息不匹配** — spec 要求 `ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")`，当前实现为 `\"sandbox not found\"`\n3. **List 方法性能不足** — spec 要求 `ListExpiredSandboxes`/`ListInactiveSandboxes` 使用 Pipeline/MGET 批量加载 sandbox 数据，当前实现使用循环逐个 GET（N+1 查询）\n4. **缺少 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` 辅助方法** — spec 要求 Valkey 实现使用 MGET 批量加载，当前实现逐个 GET\n5. **参数类型不一致** — spec 定义 `limit int64`，当前实现为 `limit int`\n6. **StoreSandbox 缺少 ExpiresAt 零值校验** — spec 要求拒绝 `ExpiresAt` 为零的 sandbox\n\n这些偏差会导致：下游组件按 spec 调用时编译失败；大规模 sandbox 场景下 List 查询性能退化；错误处理语义不统一。\n\n## Proposed Solution","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775835746378,"end":1775835746385}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775835747737,"sessionID":"ses_287f3c6b0ffeDZ0hfYvo2PU9oI","part":{"id":"prt_d780f10dc001fErzaizEO46oEF","messageID":"msg_d780f0662001uOb3LXM6vMMOkw","sessionID":"ses_287f3c6b0ffeDZ0hfYvo2PU9oI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a3eccefa0c514627a0655c4f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 — Redis Storage Implementation — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This document specifies the Redis backend implementation for the `pkg/store` session storage module in AgentCube. It provides a concrete `Store` interface implementation using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`, persisting sandbox metadata as JSON strings and maintaining sorted-set indices for garbage collection workflows.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 Redis Data Architecture\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    redisStore                           │\n14: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n15: │  │  cli: *redisv9.Client                             │  │\n16: │  │  sessionPrefix:        \"session:\"                 │  │\n17: │  │  expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\"           │  │\n18: │  │  lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"    │  │\n19: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n20: └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘\n21:                         │\n22:                         ▼\n23: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n24: │                      Redis Server                       │\n25: │                                                         │\n26: │  String Keys:                                           │\n27: │    session:{sessionID} → JSON(SandboxInfo)              │\n28: │                                                         │\n29: │  Sorted Sets:                                           │\n30: │    session:expiry          ZSET { sessionID: score }    │\n31: │      score = ExpiresAt.Unix()                           │\n32: │                                                         │\n33: │    session:last_activity   ZSET { sessionID: score }    │\n34: │      score = lastActivityAt.Unix()                      │\n35: │                                                         │\n36: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### 1.3 Package Layout\n40: \n41: ```\n42: pkg/store/\n43: ├── store.go                  # Store interface (shared)\n44: ├── singleton.go              # Provider selection (shared)\n45: ├── store_redis.go            # Redis implementation ← AR-013\n46: ├── store_redis_test.go       # Redis unit tests ← AR-013\n47: └── codec.go                  # JSON encode/decode helpers (shared)\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### 1.4 Dependencies\n51: \n52: | Module | Version | Purpose |\n53: |--------|---------|---------|\n54: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.18.0 | Redis client library |\n55: | `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | v2.37.0 | In-memory Redis for testing |\n56: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | — | `SandboxInfo` type |\n57: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Structured logging |\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 2. Data Model\n62: \n63: ### 2.1 Redis Store Struct\n64: \n65: ```go\n66: type redisStore struct {\n67:     cli                  *redisv9.Client\n68:     sessionPrefix        string\n69:     expiryIndexKey       string\n70:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n71: }\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### 2.2 Key Constants\n75: \n76: | Constant | Value | Purpose |\n77: |----------|-------|---------|\n78: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session JSON string keys |\n79: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET for expiry-based GC queries |\n80: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET for activity-based GC queries |\n81: \n82: ### 2.3 Redis Key Patterns\n83: \n84: | Key Pattern | Type | Content |\n85: |-------------|------|---------|\n86: | `session:{sessionID}` | String | JSON-marshaled `SandboxInfo` |\n87: | `session:expiry` | Sorted Set | Member: `sessionID`, Score: `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n88: | `session:last_activity` | Sorted Set | Member: `sessionID`, Score: `LastActivityAt.Unix()` |\n89: \n90: ### 2.4 SandboxInfo JSON Schema\n91: \n92: Stored as JSON string at `session:{sessionID}`:\n93: \n94: ```json\n95: {\n96:   \"kind\": \"Sandbox\",\n97:   \"sandboxId\": \"uuid-string\",\n98:   \"sandboxNamespace\": \"default\",\n99:   \"name\": \"sandbox-name\",\n100:   \"entryPoints\": [\n101:     {\n102:       \"path\": \"/api\",\n103:       \"protocol\": \"http\",\n104:       \"endpoint\": \"10.0.0.1:8080\"\n105:     }\n106:   ],\n107:   \"sessionId\": \"session-abc-123\",\n108:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-10T07:00:00Z\",\n109:   \"expiresAt\": \"2026-04-10T08:00:00Z\",\n110:   \"status\": \"Running\"\n111: }\n112: ```\n113: \n114: ### 2.5 Sorted Set Score Semantics\n115: \n116: | Index | Score Source | When Written |\n117: |-------|-------------|--------------|\n118: | `session:expiry` | `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n119: | `session:last_activity` | `float64(time.Now().Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n120: | `session:last_activity` | `float64(at.Unix())` or `time.Now()` | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` |\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 3. Interfaces\n125: \n126: ### 3.1 Store Interface Implementation\n127: \n128: `redisStore` implements the `Store` interface:\n129: \n130: ```go\n131: type Store interface {\n132:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n133:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n134:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n135:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n136:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n137:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n138:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n139:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n140:     Close() error\n141: }\n142: ```\n143: \n144: ### 3.2 Method Specifications\n145: \n146: #### 3.2.1 Ping\n147: \n148: | Aspect | Detail |\n149: |--------|--------|\n150: | Redis Command | `PING` |\n151: | Success | Response equals `\"PONG\"` |\n152: | Error | Connection error propagated |\n153: \n154: ```go\n155: func (rs *redisStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n156:     return rs.cli.Ping(ctx).Err()\n157: }\n158: ```\n159: \n160: #### 3.2.2 GetSandboxBySessionID\n161: \n162: | Aspect | Detail |\n163: |--------|--------|\n164: | Key | `session:{sessionID}` |\n165: | Redis Command | `GET` |\n166: | Not Found | `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n167: | Success | JSON unmarshal to `*types.SandboxInfo` |\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: func (rs *redisStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n171:     key := rs.sessionKey(sessionID)\n172:     data, err := rs.cli.Get(ctx, key).Result()\n173:     if err == redis.Nil {\n174:         return nil, ErrNotFound\n175:     }\n176:     if err != nil {\n177:         return nil, err\n178:     }\n179:     return decodeSandboxInfo([]byte(data))\n180: }\n181: ```\n182: \n183: #### 3.2.3 StoreSandbox\n184: \n185: | Aspect | Detail |\n186: |--------|--------|\n187: | Validation | Reject nil sandbox; reject zero `ExpiresAt` |\n188: | Redis Commands | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD` (expiry), `ZADD` (activity) |\n189: | Atomicity | All commands in pipeline; any failure aborts batch |\n190: | Idempotency | `SETNX` prevents overwriting existing session |\n191: \n192: ```go\n193: func (rs *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n194:     if sandbox == nil {\n195:         return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n196:     }\n197:     if sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n198:         return errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")\n199:     }\n200: \n201:     data, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n202:     if err != nil {\n203:         return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n204:     }\n205: \n206:     key := rs.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n207:     now := float64(time.Now().Unix())\n208:     expiryScore := float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n209: \n210:     pipe := rs.cli.Pipeline()\n211:     pipe.SetNX(ctx, key, data, 0)\n212:     pipe.ZAdd(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, redisv9.Z{Score: expiryScore, Member: sandbox.SessionID})\n213:     pipe.ZAdd(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, redisv9.Z{Score: now, Member: sandbox.SessionID})\n214: \n215:     _, err = pipe.Exec(ctx)\n216:     return err\n217: }\n218: ```\n219: \n220: #### 3.2.4 UpdateSandbox\n221: \n222: | Aspect | Detail |\n223: |--------|--------|\n224: | Redis Command | `SET key value XX` (key must exist) |\n225: | Not Found | Returns `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` |\n226: | Side Effects | Does NOT modify ZSET entries |\n227: \n228: ```go\n229: func (rs *redisStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n230:     if sandbox == nil {\n231:         return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n232:     }\n233: \n234:     data, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n235:     if err != nil {\n236:         return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n237:     }\n238: \n239:     key := rs.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n240:     ok, err := rs.cli.SetXX(ctx, key, data, 0).Result()\n241:     if err != nil {\n242:         return err\n243:     }\n244:     if !ok {\n245:         return fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)\n246:     }\n247:     return nil\n248: }\n249: ```\n250: \n251: #### 3.2.5 DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n252: \n253: | Aspect | Detail |\n254: |--------|--------|\n255: | Redis Commands | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM` (expiry), `ZREM` (activity) |\n256: | Atomicity | All commands in single pipeline |\n257: \n258: ```go\n259: func (rs *redisStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n260:     key := rs.sessionKey(sessionID)\n261:     pipe := rs.cli.Pipeline()\n262:     pipe.Del(ctx, key)\n263:     pipe.ZRem(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, sessionID)\n264:     pipe.ZRem(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, sessionID)\n265:     _, err := pipe.Exec(ctx)\n266:     return err\n267: }\n268: ```\n269: \n270: #### 3.2.6 ListExpiredSandboxes\n271: \n272: | Aspect | Detail |\n273: |--------|--------|\n274: | Precondition | `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil` |\n275: | Redis Command | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 limit` |\n276: | Follow-up | Pipeline `GET` for each session ID |\n277: | Missing Keys | Orphan ZSET members skipped (not errors) |\n278: \n279: ```go\n280: func (rs *redisStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n281:     if limit <= 0 {\n282:         return nil, nil\n283:     }\n284: \n285:     sessionIDs, err := rs.cli.ZRangeByScore(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, &redisv9.ZRangeBy{\n286:         Min:   \"-inf\",\n287:         Max:   fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()),\n288:         Count: limit,\n289:     }).Result()\n290:     if err != nil {\n291:         return nil, err\n292:     }\n293: \n294:     return rs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n295: }\n296: ```\n297: \n298: #### 3.2.7 ListInactiveSandboxes\n299: \n300: | Aspect | Detail |\n301: |--------|--------|\n302: | Same as ListExpiredSandboxes | Queries `session:last_activity` ZSET |\n303: \n304: ```go\n305: func (rs *redisStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n306:     if limit <= 0 {\n307:         return nil, nil\n308:     }\n309: \n310:     sessionIDs, err := rs.cli.ZRangeByScore(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, &redisv9.ZRangeBy{\n311:         Min:   \"-inf\",\n312:         Max:   fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()),\n313:         Count: limit,\n314:     }).Result()\n315:     if err != nil {\n316:         return nil, err\n317:     }\n318: \n319:     return rs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n320: }\n321: ```\n322: \n323: #### 3.2.8 UpdateSessionLastActivity\n324: \n325: | Aspect | Detail |\n326: |--------|--------|\n327: | Validation | Reject empty `sessionID` |\n328: | Zero Time | If `at.IsZero()`, use `time.Now()` |\n329: | Precondition | Session key must exist; absent → `ErrNotFound` |\n330: | Redis Commands | `EXISTS` → `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n331: \n332: ```go\n333: func (rs *redisStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n334:     if sessionID == \"\" {\n335:         return errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")\n336:     }\n337:     if at.IsZero() {\n338:         at = time.Now()\n339:     }\n340: \n341:     key := rs.sessionKey(sessionID)\n342:     exists, err := rs.cli.Exists(ctx, key).Result()\n343:     if err != nil {\n344:         return err\n345:     }\n346:     if exists == 0 {\n347:         return ErrNotFound\n348:     }\n349: \n350:     return rs.cli.ZAdd(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, redisv9.Z{\n351:         Score:  float64(at.Unix()),\n352:         Member: sessionID,\n353:     }).Err()\n354: }\n355: ```\n356: \n357: #### 3.2.9 Close\n358: \n359: ```go\n360: func (rs *redisStore) Close() error {\n361:     return rs.cli.Close()\n362: }\n363: ```\n364: \n365: ### 3.3 Helper Functions\n366: \n367: #### 3.3.1 sessionKey\n368: \n369: ```go\n370: func (rs *redisStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n371:     return rs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n372: }\n373: ```\n374: \n375: #### 3.3.2 loadSandboxesBySessionIDs\n376: \n377: ```go\n378: func (rs *redisStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n379:     if len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n380:         return nil, nil\n381:     }\n382: \n383:     keys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n384:     for i, id := range sessionIDs {\n385:         keys[i] = rs.sessionKey(id)\n386:     }\n387: \n388:     results, err := rs.cli.MGet(ctx, keys...).Result()\n389:     if err != nil {\n390:         return nil, err\n391:     }\n392: \n393:     var sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\n394:     for _, raw := range results {\n395:         if raw == nil {\n396:             continue // Skip orphan ZSET members\n397:         }\n398:         data, ok := raw.(string)\n399:         if !ok || data == \"\" {\n400:             continue\n401:         }\n402:         sandbox, err := decodeSandboxInfo([]byte(data))\n403:         if err != nil {\n404:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n405:         }\n406:         sandboxes = append(sandboxes, sandbox)\n407:     }\n408:     return sandboxes, nil\n409: }\n410: ```\n411: \n412: ### 3.4 Constructor\n413: \n414: ```go\n415: func newRedisStore() (*redisStore, error) {\n416:     redisAddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n417:     if redisAddr == \"\" {\n418:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n419:     }\n420: \n421:     redisPassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n422:     passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n423:     if redisPassword == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n424:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required (set REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n425:     }\n426: \n427:     opts := &redisv9.Options{\n428:         Addr:     redisAddr,\n429:         Password: redisPassword,\n430:     }\n431: \n432:     cli := redisv9.NewClient(opts)\n433:     if err := cli.Ping(context.Background()).Err(); err != nil {\n434:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"redis ping failed: %w\", err)\n435:     }\n436: \n437:     return &redisStore{\n438:         cli:                  cli,\n439:         sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n440:         expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n441:         lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n442:     }, nil\n443: }\n444: ```\n445: \n446: ---\n447: \n448: ## 4. Error Handling\n449: \n450: ### 4.1 Error Types\n451: \n452: | Error | Source | Handling |\n453: |-------|--------|----------|\n454: | `ErrNotFound` | Package sentinel | Returned when session key absent |\n455: | `redis.Nil` | go-redis | Normalized to `ErrNotFound` |\n456: | Pipeline errors | `pipe.Exec()` | Propagated directly |\n457: | Validation errors | Input checks | Descriptive `errors.New()` messages |\n458: | Connection errors | Redis client | Propagated with context |\n459: \n460: ### 4.2 Error Handling Matrix\n461: \n462: | Scenario | Error Returned | Notes |\n463: |----------|---------------|-------|\n464: | Session key not found | `ErrNotFound` | `redis.Nil` normalized |\n465: | Nil sandbox to StoreSandbox | `errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")` | Input validation |\n466: | Zero ExpiresAt | `errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")` | Input validation |\n467: | Empty sessionID | `errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")` | UpdateSessionLastActivity |\n468: | UpdateSandbox missing key | `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` | SETXX returns false |\n469: | Pipeline command failure | Backend error | Batch aborts |\n470: | Missing REDIS_ADDR | `errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")` | Constructor |\n471: | Missing REDIS_PASSWORD | `errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required ...\")` | Unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n472: | Redis ping failure | `fmt.Errorf(\"redis ping failed: %w\", err)` | Constructor |\n473: \n474: ### 4.3 Environment Variables\n475: \n476: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n477: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n478: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | — | Redis server address |\n479: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | — | Auth password |\n480: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive `\"false\"` disables |\n481: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `redis` or unset for this backend |\n482: \n483: ---\n484: \n485: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n486: \n487: ### 5.1 Unit Test Matrix\n488: \n489: #### Test Helper Setup\n490: \n491: ```go\n492: func newTestRedisStore(t *testing.T) (*redisStore, *miniredis.Miniredis) {\n493:     t.Helper()\n494:     mr, err := miniredis.Run()\n495:     require.NoError(t, err)\n496:     t.Cleanup(func() { mr.Close() })\n497: \n498:     cli := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{Addr: mr.Addr()})\n499:     t.Cleanup(func() { cli.Close() })\n500: \n501:     return &redisStore{\n502:         cli:                  cli,\n503:         sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n504:         expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n505:         lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n506:     }, mr\n507: }\n508: \n509: func testSandboxInfo(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n510:     now := time.Now().UTC()\n511:     return &types.SandboxInfo{\n512:         SessionID:      sessionID,\n513:         SandboxName:    \"test-sandbox\",\n514:         SandboxID:      uuid.New().String(),\n515:         Namespace:      \"default\",\n516:         Kind:           \"Sandbox\",\n517:         CreatedAt:      now,\n518:         ExpiresAt:      now.Add(1 * time.Hour),\n519:         Status:         \"Running\",\n520:         LastActivityAt: now,\n521:     }\n522: }\n523: ```\n524: \n525: #### Test Cases\n526: \n527: | Test Name | Description | Assertions |\n528: |-----------|-------------|------------|\n529: | `TestRedisStore_Ping_Success` | PING → PONG | `require.NoError` |\n530: | `TestRedisStore_Ping_Failure` | Bad connection | `assert.Error` |\n531: | `TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_Found` | Store then get | `assert.Equal` on SessionID |\n532: | `TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | Missing key | `assert.ErrorIs(ErrNotFound)` |\n533: | `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Success` | Full pipeline | Key exists, ZSET members added |\n534: | `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected` | nil input | `assert.Error` |\n535: | `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` | Zero ExpiresAt | `assert.Error` |\n536: | `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Idempotent` | Double store | Second call doesn't overwrite |\n537: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_Success` | SETXX updates | JSON changed, ZSET unchanged |\n538: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | No prior store | `assert.Error` contains \"key not exists\" |\n539: | `TestRedisStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Full cleanup | Key deleted, ZSET members removed |\n540: | `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` | Query by expiry | Returns expired, not active |\n541: | `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ZeroLimit` | limit=0 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n542: | `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanMember` | ZSET member without key | Skipped, not error |\n543: | `TestRedisStore_ListInactiveSandboxes` | Query by activity | Returns inactive, not active |\n544: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_Success` | Valid session | ZADD with new score |\n545: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound` | Missing session | `assert.ErrorIs(ErrNotFound)` |\n546: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime` | `at.IsZero()` | Uses `time.Now()` |\n547: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_EmptyID` | Empty sessionID | `assert.Error` |\n548: | `TestRedisStore_Close` | Connection closed | No error |\n549: \n550: ### 5.2 Test Implementation Examples\n551: \n552: #### Ping Test\n553: \n554: ```go\n555: func TestRedisStore_Ping_Success(t *testing.T) {\n556:     store, _ := newTestRedisStore(t)\n557:     err := store.Ping(context.Background())\n558:     require.NoError(t, err)\n559: }\n560: ```\n561: \n562: #### StoreSandbox Test\n563: \n564: ```go\n565: func TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Success(t *testing.T) {\n566:     store, mr := newTestRedisStore(t)\n567:     sandbox := testSandboxInfo(\"test-session\")\n568: \n569:     err := store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), sandbox)\n570:     require.NoError(t, err)\n571: \n572:     // Verify string key\n573:     key := store.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n574:     data, err := mr.Get(key)\n575:     require.NoError(t, err)\n576:     assert.Contains(t, data, sandbox.SessionID)\n577: \n578:     // Verify ZSET entries\n579:     expiryScore, err := mr.ZScore(\"session:expiry\", sandbox.SessionID)\n580:     require.NoError(t, err)\n581:     assert.Equal(t, float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix()), expiryScore)\n582: \n583:     activityScore, err := mr.ZScore(\"session:last_activity\", sandbox.SessionID)\n584:     require.NoError(t, err)\n585:     assert.InDelta(t, float64(time.Now().Unix()), activityScore, 1.0)\n586: }\n587: ```\n588: \n589: #### ListExpiredSandboxes Orphan Test\n590: \n591: ```go\n592: func TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanMember(t *testing.T) {\n593:     store, mr := newTestRedisStore(t)\n594: \n595:     // Add orphan ZSET member without corresponding string key\n596:     mr.ZAdd(\"session:expiry\", \"orphan-session\", float64(time.Now().Add(-1*time.Hour).Unix()))\n597: \n598:     result, err := store.ListExpiredSandboxes(context.Background(), time.Now(), 10)\n599:     require.NoError(t, err)\n600:     assert.Empty(t, result) // Orphan skipped\n601: }\n602: ```\n603: \n604: ### 5.3 Integration Tests\n605: \n606: | Test Name | Description | Requirements |\n607: |-----------|-------------|--------------|\n608: | `TestRedisStore_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Store → Get → Update → List → Delete | Real Redis instance |\n609: | `TestRedisStore_GC_Workflow` | Store expired, list, delete | Real Redis instance |\n610: \n611: ### 5.4 Gate Requirements\n612: \n613: 1. `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles\n614: 2. `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` all pass\n615: 3. `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` no data race warnings\n616: 4. No `log.Printf` usage (use klog)\n617: 5. No sensitive data in logs (passwords, connection strings)\n618: 6. Test coverage ≥ 80% for `store_redis.go`\n619: \n620: ---\n621: \n622: ## 6. Deployment Considerations\n623: \n624: ### 6.1 Connection Pooling\n625: \n626: Default go-redis pool settings:\n627: - `PoolSize`: 10 × number of CPUs\n628: - `MinIdleConns`: 0\n629: - `MaxConnAge`: 0 (no limit)\n630: - `PoolTimeout`: 4 seconds\n631: - `IdleTimeout`: 5 minutes\n632: \n633: Tune via environment-specific configuration if needed.\n634: \n635: ### 6.2 Password Policy\n636: \n637: Password required by default. Set `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` only in trusted network environments (e.g., VPC with security groups).\n638: \n639: ### 6.3 ZSET Index Growth\n640: \n641: `session:expiry` and `session:last_activity` sorted sets grow monotonically. Ensure the GC controller regularly calls:\n642: - `ListExpiredSandboxes` → `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n643: - `ListInactiveSandboxes` → `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n644: \n645: Monitor ZSET cardinality via `ZCARD` commands.\n646: \n647: ### 6.4 Memory Considerations\n648: \n649: - Session JSON strings: ~500 bytes per sandbox\n650: - ZSET entries: ~100 bytes per session ID per index\n651: - Estimated memory: ~700 bytes × number of active sessions\n652: \n653: ### 6.5 Redis Cluster\n654: \n655: For Redis Cluster deployments:\n656: - Consider hash tags for key slot affinity: `session:{cluster}:{sessionID}`\n657: - `MGET` in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` requires keys in same slot\n658: - Pipeline commands may cross slots; monitor `CROSSSLOT` errors\n659: \n660: ---\n661: \n662: ## 7. Implementation Steps\n663: \n664: ### Phase 1: Core Implementation (Day 1)\n665: \n666: 1. Implement `redisStore` struct in `store_redis.go`\n667: 2. Implement constructor with environment variable validation\n668: 3. Implement `Ping`, `Close`, `sessionKey` helper\n669: \n670: ### Phase 2: CRUD Operations (Day 2)\n671: \n672: 1. Implement `StoreSandbox` with pipeline\n673: 2. Implement `UpdateSandbox` with SETXX\n674: 3. Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` with pipeline\n675: 4. Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID` with ErrNotFound handling\n676: \n677: ### Phase 3: Query Operations (Day 3)\n678: \n679: 1. Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` helper\n680: 2. Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes`\n681: 3. Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n682: 4. Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n683: \n684: ### Phase 4: Testing & Validation (Day 4)\n685: \n686: 1. Write unit tests with miniredis\n687: 2. Run `go test -race ./pkg/store/...`\n688: 3. Verify test coverage\n689: 4. Fix all issues\n690: \n691: ---\n692: \n693: ## 8. Future Changes\n694: \n695: | Change | Description | Priority |\n696: |--------|-------------|----------|\n697: | AR-0XX | TTL on session keys for automatic cleanup | P1 |\n698: | AR-0XX | Hash tag support for Redis Cluster slot affinity | P2 |\n699: | AR-0XX | Metrics: store operation latency, error rates | P2 |\n700: | AR-0XX | Connection pool tuning via environment variables | P3 |\n701: \n702: ### Known Limitations\n703: \n704: - No automatic TTL on session JSON keys; relies on GC controller for cleanup\n705: - `MGET` in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` assumes single-slot keys for cluster deployments\n706: - No pagination for `List*` methods beyond simple `limit` parameter\n707: - `SETNX` in `StoreSandbox` prevents updates; use `UpdateSandbox` for modifications\n\n(End of file - total 707 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013 — Redis Storage Implementation — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis document specifies the Redis backend implementation for the `pkg/store` session storage module in AgentCube. It provides a concrete `Store` interface implementation using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`, persisting sandbox metadata as JSON strings and maintaining sorted-set indices for garbage collection workflows.\n\n### 1.2 Redis Data Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    redisStore                           │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  cli: *redisv9.Client                             │  │\n│  │  sessionPrefix:        \"session:\"                 │  │\n│  │  expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\"           │  │\n│  │  lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"    │  │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/design.md","time":{"start":1775835747728,"end":1775835747734}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775835749073,"sessionID":"ses_287f3c6b0ffeDZ0hfYvo2PU9oI","part":{"id":"prt_d780f161e001S16013t7kgDPVo","messageID":"msg_d780f0662001uOb3LXM6vMMOkw","sessionID":"ses_287f3c6b0ffeDZ0hfYvo2PU9oI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_17ddd8ffd8b641639856c518","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** pkg/store\n4: > **Language:** Go\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-013/design.md`, `changes/AR-013/proposal.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n8: \n9: ## T1. 修正 ErrNotFound 错误消息\n10: \n11: - [ ] 1.1 将 `store.go` 中 `ErrNotFound` 从 `\"sandbox not found\"` 改为 `\"store: not found\"`\n12: - [ ] 1.2 更新 `store_redis_test.go` 中依赖旧错误消息的断言（如有）\n13: - [ ] 1.3 运行 `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` 确认全部通过\n14: \n15: **Verification:** `grep \"store: not found\" pkg/store/store.go` 匹配；`go test ./pkg/store/...` 全绿\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## T2. 修正 Store 接口签名\n20: \n21: - [ ] 2.1 将 `GetSandbox` 重命名为 `GetSandboxBySessionID`\n22: - [ ] 2.2 将 `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo)` 改为 `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo)`\n23: - [ ] 2.3 将 `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo)` 改为 `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo)`\n24: - [ ] 2.4 将 `ListExpiredSandboxes` 和 `ListInactiveSandboxes` 的 `limit int` 改为 `limit int64`\n25: - [ ] 2.5 运行 `go build ./pkg/store/...` 确认编译通过\n26: \n27: **Verification:** `Store` 接口签名与 `design.md` §3.1 完全一致；`go build ./pkg/store/...` 零错误\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## T3. 重构 Redis 实现对齐新接口\n32: \n33: - [ ] 3.1 将 `redisStore` 的 `cli` 字段类型从 `redis.UniversalClient` 改为 `*redis.Client`（即 design 中的 `*redisv9.Client`）\n34: - [ ] 3.2 新增 `sessionKey(sessionID string) string` 辅助方法，替换所有 `r.sessionPrefix + sessionID` 内联拼接\n35: - [ ] 3.3 重构 `GetSandbox` → `GetSandboxBySessionID`，使用 `sessionKey()` 辅助方法\n36: - [ ] 3.4 重构 `StoreSandbox`：从 `sandbox.SessionID` 提取 sessionID，使用 `sessionKey()` 辅助方法\n37: - [ ] 3.5 重构 `UpdateSandbox`：从 `sandbox.SessionID` 提取 sessionID，使用 `sessionKey()` 辅助方法\n38: - [ ] 3.6 重构 `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`：使用 `sessionKey()` 辅助方法\n39: - [ ] 3.7 重构 `ListExpiredSandboxes` 和 `ListInactiveSandboxes`：`limit` 参数改为 `int64`，移除 `strconv.FormatInt` 转换（直接用 `fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())`）\n40: - [ ] 3.8 运行 `go build ./pkg/store/...` 确认编译通过\n41: \n42: **Verification:** `store_redis.go` 中无 `r.sessionPrefix +` 内联拼接；所有方法签名与 T2 接口一致；`go build` 零错误\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## T4. StoreSandbox 增加 ExpiresAt 零值校验\n47: \n48: - [ ] 4.1 在 `StoreSandbox` 方法开头增加 `sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero()` 校验\n49: - [ ] 4.2 零值时返回 `errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")`\n50: - [ ] 4.3 新增单元测试 `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry`\n51: - [ ] 4.4 确认 `StoreSandbox` 的 `lastActivityScore` 使用 `time.Now().Unix()` 而非 `info.LastActivityAt.Unix()`（对齐 design §2.5）\n52: \n53: **Verification:** `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` 通过；design §3.2.3 代码与实现一致\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## T5. 新增 loadSandboxesBySessionIDs 辅助方法\n58: \n59: - [ ] 5.1 实现 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n60: - [ ] 5.2 使用 `MGet` 批量获取（design §3.3.2）\n61: - [ ] 5.3 跳过 nil 结果（orphan ZSET member 容错）\n62: - [ ] 5.4 跳过空字符串或类型断言失败的结果\n63: - [ ] 5.5 新增单元测试 `TestRedisStore_LoadSandboxesBySessionIDs_Empty`\n64: - [ ] 5.6 新增单元测试 `TestRedisStore_LoadSandboxesBySessionIDs_OrphanSkipped`\n65: - [ ] 5.7 新增单元测试 `TestRedisStore_LoadSandboxesBySessionIDs_BatchSuccess`\n66: \n67: **Verification:** 方法签名与 design §3.3.2 一致；orphan 场景测试通过；MGet 单次调用而非循环 GET\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## T6. 重构 ListExpiredSandboxes 和 ListInactiveSandboxes 使用 loadSandboxesBySessionIDs\n72: \n73: - [ ] 6.1 `ListExpiredSandboxes` 移除循环 GET 逻辑，改为调用 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs`\n74: - [ ] 6.2 `ListInactiveSandboxes` 移除循环 GET 逻辑，改为调用 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs`\n75: - [ ] 6.3 确认 `ZRANGEBYSCORE` 使用 `redis.ZRangeBy` 结构体（`Min: \"-inf\"`, `Max: fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())`, `Count: limit`）\n76: - [ ] 6.4 确认现有 orphan 测试用例仍然通过\n77: - [ ] 6.5 确认 limit 边界测试用例仍然通过（0、负数、正数）\n78: \n79: **Verification:** 两个 List 方法体内无 `for _, id := range sessionIDs { GetSandbox ... }` 循环；所有现有 List 测试通过\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## T7. 重构构造函数 newRedisStore 返回 error\n84: \n85: - [ ] 7.1 将 `newRedisStore() Store` 改为 `newRedisStore() (*redisStore, error)`\n86: - [ ] 7.2 移除 `klog.Fatal()` 调用，改为返回 `error`\n87: - [ ] 7.3 `REDIS_ADDR` 为空时返回 `errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")`\n88: - [ ] 7.4 `REDIS_PASSWORD` 为空且 `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED != \"false\"` 时返回 `errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required (set REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")`\n89: - [ ] 7.5 增加 `cli.Ping(ctx)` 验证连接，失败返回 `fmt.Errorf(\"redis ping failed: %w\", err)`\n90: - [ ] 7.6 更新 `singleton.go` 中 `initStore()` 对 `newRedisStore()` 的调用，处理返回的 error\n91: - [ ] 7.7 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewRedisStore_MissingAddr`\n92: - [ ] 7.8 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewRedisStore_MissingPassword`\n93: - [ ] 7.9 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewRedisStore_PasswordBypassed`\n94: \n95: **Verification:** `newRedisStore` 签名返回 `(*redisStore, error)`；无 `klog.Fatal` 调用；singleton.go 正确处理 error；构造测试全绿\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## T8. 更新 Redis 单元测试适配新接口\n100: \n101: - [ ] 8.1 更新 `newTestRedisStore` 中 `cli` 字段类型为 `*redis.Client`\n102: - [ ] 8.2 更新所有 `StoreSandbox` 调用：从 `StoreSandbox(ctx, \"sid\", info)` 改为 `StoreSandbox(ctx, info)`\n103: - [ ] 8.3 更新所有 `UpdateSandbox` 调用：从 `UpdateSandbox(ctx, \"sid\", info)` 改为 `UpdateSandbox(ctx, info)`\n104: - [ ] 8.4 更新所有 `GetSandbox` 调用为 `GetSandboxBySessionID`\n105: - [ ] 8.5 更新 `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_NilInfo` 错误消息断言为 `\"sandbox is nil\"`\n106: - [ ] 8.6 新增 `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Idempotent`（SETNX 幂等性验证）\n107: - [ ] 8.7 新增 `TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey` 验证返回错误包含 `\"key not exists\"`\n108: - [ ] 8.8 运行 `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -count=1` 全部通过\n109: \n110: **Verification:** 测试文件中无旧签名调用；`go test ./pkg/store/... -v` 全绿；测试覆盖率 ≥ 80%（`go test -cover ./pkg/store/...`）\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## T9. 竞态检测与门禁验证\n115: \n116: - [ ] 9.1 运行 `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` 无 data race 警告\n117: - [ ] 9.2 确认无 `log.Printf` 使用（仅允许 `klog`）\n118: - [ ] 9.3 确认日志中无敏感数据（密码、连接字符串）\n119: - [ ] 9.4 运行 `go vet ./pkg/store/...` 无警告\n120: - [ ] 9.5 确认 `go build ./pkg/store/...` 编译通过\n121: \n122: **Verification:** 以上 5 项全部通过\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Task Dependencies\n127: \n128: ```\n129: T1 ──┐\n130: T2 ──┼──→ T3 ──┬──→ T4\n131:      │         ├──→ T5 ──→ T6\n132:      │         └──→ T7\n133:      │\n134: T8 ────────────────→ (depends on T1-T7 completion)\n135: T9 ────────────────→ (depends on T8 completion)\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ## Acceptance Criteria\n139: \n140: | # | Criterion | Command |\n141: |---|-----------|---------|\n142: | AC1 | 编译通过 | `go build ./pkg/store/...` |\n143: | AC2 | 全部测试通过 | `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -count=1` |\n144: | AC3 | 无竞态条件 | `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` |\n145: | AC4 | 覆盖率 ≥ 80% | `go test -cover ./pkg/store/...` |\n146: | AC5 | 无 lint 警告 | `go vet ./pkg/store/...` |\n147: | AC6 | Store 接口签名与 design.md §3.1 一致 | 代码审查 |\n148: | AC7 | `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` 使用 MGet 批量加载 | 代码审查 |\n149: | AC8 | `StoreSandbox` 拒绝零 ExpiresAt | `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` 通过 |\n150: | AC9 | 构造函数返回 error 而非 klog.Fatal | 代码审查 + 单元测试 |\n\n(End of file - total 150 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** pkg/store\n> **Language:** Go\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-013/design.md`, `changes/AR-013/proposal.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n\n## T1. 修正 ErrNotFound 错误消息\n\n- [ ] 1.1 将 `store.go` 中 `ErrNotFound` 从 `\"sandbox not found\"` 改为 `\"store: not found\"`\n- [ ] 1.2 更新 `store_redis_test.go` 中依赖旧错误消息的断言（如有）\n- [ ] 1.3 运行 `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` 确认全部通过\n\n**Verification:** `grep \"store: not found\" pkg/store/store.go` 匹配；`go test ./pkg/store/...` 全绿\n\n---\n\n## T2. 修正 Store 接口签名\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775835749062,"end":1775835749070}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775835750291,"sessionID":"ses_287f3c6b0ffeDZ0hfYvo2PU9oI","part":{"id":"prt_d780f1b55001c4zCK9KeJCSsfb","messageID":"msg_d780f0662001uOb3LXM6vMMOkw","sessionID":"ses_287f3c6b0ffeDZ0hfYvo2PU9oI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_51e66843de264c97928705dc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013: Redis 存储实现 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `pkg/store`\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `session-store/spec.md`, `session-store/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: Redis client initialization\n13: The Redis implementation SHALL construct a `redisv9.Client` using `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` environment variables. The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR` to be non-empty. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`.\n14: \n15: #### Scenario: Successful initialization with address and password\n16: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set to `\"localhost:6379\"` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` is set to `\"secret\"`\n17: - **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n18: - **THEN** a `redisv9.Client` is constructed with `Addr: \"localhost:6379\"` and `Password: \"secret\"`\n19: - **AND** no error is returned\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Missing address fails\n22: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is empty or unset\n23: - **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n24: - **THEN** initialization returns an error indicating `REDIS_ADDR` is required\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n27: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty, and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n28: - **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n29: - **THEN** initialization fails with an error stating password is required\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Password bypass when explicitly disabled\n32: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty, and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set to `\"false\"` (case-insensitive)\n33: - **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n34: - **THEN** a `redisv9.Client` is constructed with empty password\n35: - **AND** no error is returned\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Password not required when flag is not false\n38: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty, and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set to `\"true\"`\n39: - **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n40: - **THEN** initialization fails with an error stating password is required\n41: \n42: ### Requirement: Redis connection options\n43: The system SHALL build `redisv9.Options` with `Addr` from `REDIS_ADDR` and `Password` from `REDIS_PASSWORD`.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Options construction\n46: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR=\"redis-host:6380\"` and `REDIS_PASSWORD=\"pass123\"`\n47: - **WHEN** `makeRedisOptions()` is called\n48: - **THEN** the returned options have `Addr: \"redis-host:6380\"` and `Password: \"pass123\"`\n49: \n50: ### Requirement: Redis StoreSandbox pipeline\n51: The Redis implementation SHALL execute `StoreSandbox` as a pipeline of three commands: `SETNX` on the session key with JSON value, `ZADD` on `session:expiry` with score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`, and `ZADD` on `session:last_activity` with score = `time.Now().Unix()`. The system SHALL fail if any command in the pipeline returns an error.\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Successful store pipeline\n54: - **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with non-zero `ExpiresAt` and session id `s1`\n55: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called on the Redis store\n56: - **THEN** the pipeline executes `SETNX session:s1 <json>`, `ZADD session:expiry <expires_unix> s1`, `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` and returns nil\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Pipeline error propagation\n59: - **GIVEN** the Redis server is unreachable during `StoreSandbox`\n60: - **WHEN** the pipeline executes\n61: - **THEN** the method returns a non-nil error and no partial state is committed\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n64: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n65: - **WHEN** the method executes\n66: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating sandbox is nil\n67: - **AND** no Redis commands are issued\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n70: - **GIVEN** `SandboxInfo` has `ExpiresAt == time.Time{}`\n71: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n72: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating ExpiresAt is required\n73: - **AND** no Redis commands are issued\n74: \n75: ### Requirement: Redis UpdateSandbox XX semantics\n76: The Redis implementation SHALL use `SET key value XX` for `UpdateSandbox`. If the key does not exist, the system SHALL return an error indicating the key does not exist.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Update existing key\n79: - **GIVEN** session key `session:s1` exists\n80: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n81: - **THEN** the JSON value is overwritten and the method returns nil\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Update missing key\n84: - **GIVEN** session key `session:s1` does not exist\n85: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n86: - **THEN** the method returns an error containing `key not exists`\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected on update\n89: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n90: - **WHEN** the method executes\n91: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating sandbox is nil\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Redis DeleteSandboxBySessionID pipeline\n94: The Redis implementation SHALL execute `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` as a pipeline of three commands: `DEL` on the session key, `ZREM` on `session:expiry`, and `ZREM` on `session:last_activity`.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Full deletion\n97: - **GIVEN** session `s1` exists with entries in both ZSETs\n98: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` succeeds\n99: - **THEN** `GET session:s1` returns nil and both ZSETs no longer contain member `s1`\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Delete non-existent session\n102: - **GIVEN** session `ghost` does not exist\n103: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"ghost\")` is called\n104: - **THEN** the pipeline executes (DEL returns 0, ZREM returns 0) and no error is returned\n105: \n106: ### Requirement: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID\n107: The Redis implementation SHALL retrieve a sandbox document using `GET session:{id}`. If the key does not exist, the system SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Existing session retrieved\n110: - **GIVEN** a sandbox document exists at key `session:s1`\n111: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` is called\n112: - **THEN** the JSON value is unmarshaled to `*types.SandboxInfo` and returned with nil error\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Missing session returns ErrNotFound\n115: - **GIVEN** no key exists at `session:missing`\n116: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"missing\")` is called\n117: - **THEN** the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n118: \n119: ### Requirement: Redis ListExpiredSandboxes query\n120: The Redis implementation SHALL query `session:expiry` using `ZRANGEBYSCORE` with range `-inf` to `before.Unix()` and `LIMIT 0 limit`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: List with limit zero\n123: - **GIVEN** expired sessions exist in the index\n124: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` is called\n125: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil` without querying Redis\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: List with positive limit\n128: - **GIVEN** three sessions have expiry scores ≤ `before.Unix()`\n129: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 2)` is called\n130: - **THEN** at most two `SandboxInfo` pointers are returned\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: List with negative limit\n133: - **GIVEN** expired sessions exist\n134: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)` is called\n135: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil`\n136: \n137: ### Requirement: Redis ListInactiveSandboxes query\n138: The Redis implementation SHALL query `session:last_activity` using `ZRANGEBYSCORE` with range `-inf` to `before.Unix()` and `LIMIT 0 limit`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Inactive list with negative limit\n141: - **GIVEN** inactive sessions exist\n142: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)` is called\n143: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Inactive list with positive limit\n146: - **GIVEN** two sessions have last-activity scores ≤ `before.Unix()`\n147: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 5)` is called\n148: - **THEN** up to two `SandboxInfo` pointers are returned\n149: \n150: ### Requirement: Redis UpdateSessionLastActivity precondition\n151: The Redis implementation SHALL verify the session key exists via `GET` before executing `ZADD` on `session:last_activity`. If the key is absent, the method SHALL return `ErrNotFound`. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`.\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Activity update with zero time\n154: - **GIVEN** session `s1` exists and `at` is `time.Time{}`\n155: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at)` is called\n156: - **THEN** `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` is executed\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: Activity update for missing session\n159: - **GIVEN** session `s1` does not exist\n160: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", now)` is called\n161: - **THEN** the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: Empty session ID rejected\n164: - **GIVEN** empty session ID `\"\"`\n165: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at)` is called\n166: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating session ID is empty\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: Redis pipeline GET orphan tolerance\n169: The Redis implementation SHALL handle nil results from pipeline `GET` commands when loading sandboxes by session IDs. Entries with nil results SHALL be skipped without failing the batch.\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Redis orphan ZSET member\n172: - **GIVEN** session id `ghost` is in `session:last_activity` but `session:ghost` does not exist\n173: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` loads the batch via pipeline GETs\n174: - **THEN** `ghost` is omitted from the result slice\n175: - **AND** no error is raised\n176: \n177: ### Requirement: Redis Ping response validation\n178: The Redis implementation SHALL issue `PING` and validate the response equals `PONG`.\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Healthy Redis\n181: - **GIVEN** Redis server is running\n182: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n183: - **THEN** the response is `PONG` and nil error is returned\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Unreachable Redis\n186: - **GIVEN** Redis server is down\n187: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n188: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating connection failure\n189: \n190: ### Requirement: Redis Close operation\n191: The Redis implementation SHALL close the client connection via `cli.Close()`.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Client closed successfully\n194: - **GIVEN** an active Redis store\n195: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n196: - **THEN** `cli.Close()` is invoked and nil is returned\n197: \n198: ### Requirement: Redis fixed key patterns\n199: The Redis implementation SHALL use the following fixed key patterns: `sessionPrefix = \"session:\"`, `expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"`, `lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"`.\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Session key construction\n202: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n203: - **WHEN** the store constructs the key\n204: - **THEN** the key is `session:abc`\n205: \n206: ### Requirement: Redis ZSET score semantics\n207: The system SHALL use Unix seconds as scores in sorted sets. Expiry index score = `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())`. Last activity score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on store, `float64(at.Unix())` on update.\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: Expiry score is sandbox ExpiresAt\n210: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` set to a specific time T\n211: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` adds to `session:expiry`\n212: - **THEN** the score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Last activity score is current time on store\n215: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox` is called at time T\n216: - **WHEN** the sandbox is added to `session:last_activity`\n217: - **THEN** the score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n218: \n219: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n220: When `STORE_TYPE` is unset or empty, the system SHALL default to `redis` (case-insensitive comparison). Supported values are `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Unset STORE_TYPE defaults to redis\n223: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` environment variable is not set\n224: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n225: - **THEN** the Redis implementation is constructed\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE\n228: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=memcached`\n229: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n230: - **THEN** initialization fails with an unsupported store type error\n231: \n232: ### Requirement: Singleton initialization\n233: The system SHALL use `sync.Once` to ensure `initStore` executes exactly once. `Storage()` SHALL call `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)` and on error SHALL call `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: Concurrent Storage calls\n236: - **GIVEN** ten goroutines call `Storage()` simultaneously\n237: - **WHEN** all calls complete\n238: - **THEN** `initStore` has executed exactly once and all goroutines receive the same `Store` instance\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: Failed initialization is fatal\n241: - **GIVEN** required environment variables are missing\n242: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n243: - **THEN** `klog.Fatalf` is invoked with message `\"init store failed: %v\"`\n244: - **AND** the process terminates\n\n(End of file - total 244 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013: Redis 存储实现 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `pkg/store`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `session-store/spec.md`, `session-store/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Redis client initialization\nThe Redis implementation SHALL construct a `redisv9.Client` using `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` environment variables. The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR` to be non-empty. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful initialization with address and password\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set to `\"localhost:6379\"` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` is set to `\"secret\"`\n- **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** a `redisv9.Client` is constructed with `Addr: \"localhost:6379\"` and `Password: \"secret\"`\n- **AND** no error is returned\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775835750284,"end":1775835750289}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775835751515,"sessionID":"ses_287f3c6b0ffeDZ0hfYvo2PU9oI","part":{"id":"prt_d780f201d001RHEn03skQeixw6","messageID":"msg_d780f0662001uOb3LXM6vMMOkw","sessionID":"ses_287f3c6b0ffeDZ0hfYvo2PU9oI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_492926ad5a074052bea1fb45","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/client-go.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/client-go.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # client-go library\n2: \n3: Generated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n4: \n5: ## Clientset\n6: \n7: ### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n8: \n9: ```go\n10: type Interface interface {\n11: \tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n12: \tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n13: }\n14: ```\n15: \n16: ### `Clientset` struct\n17: \n18: Embeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n19: \n20: **Constructors**\n21: \n22: - `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n23: - `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n24: - `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n25: - `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n26: \n27: **Group accessor:** `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Typed client — `runtime/v1alpha1`\n32: \n33: ### `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n34: \n35: ```go\n36: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n37: \tRESTClient() rest.Interface\n38: \tAgentRuntimesGetter\n39: \tCodeInterpretersGetter\n40: }\n41: ```\n42: \n43: `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` implements this interface. REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`, negotiated serializer from `clientset/versioned/scheme`.\n44: \n45: ### `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `AgentRuntimeInterface` (`.../agentruntime.go`)\n46: \n47: ```go\n48: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n49: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n50: }\n51: \n52: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n53: \tCreate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n54: \tUpdate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n55: \tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n56: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n57: \tDeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n58: \tGet(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n59: \tList(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n60: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n61: \tPatch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n62: \tAgentRuntimeExpansion\n63: }\n64: ```\n65: \n66: REST resource plural: **`agentruntimes`**.\n67: \n68: ### `CodeInterpretersGetter` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` (`.../codeinterpreter.go`)\n69: \n70: Same method shape as `AgentRuntimeInterface`, types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: **`codeinterpreters`**.\n71: \n72: ### Expansion hooks (`generated_expansion.go`)\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: type AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\n76: type CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n77: ```\n78: \n79: (Empty — reserved for custom methods.)\n80: \n81: ### Fake clients (`typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/`)\n82: \n83: `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` — test doubles implementing the typed interfaces; `doc.go` markers.\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## Scheme (`clientset/versioned/scheme/`)\n88: \n89: | File | Role |\n90: |------|------|\n91: | `register.go` | Builds `Scheme`, `Codecs`, `ParameterCodec`; `AddToScheme` registers `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n92: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Informer factory\n97: \n98: ### `SharedInformerFactory` (`informers/externalversions/factory.go`)\n99: \n100: ```go\n101: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n102: \tinternalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n103: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n104: \tShutdown()\n105: \tWaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n106: \tForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n107: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n108: \tRuntime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n109: }\n110: ```\n111: \n112: **Constructors / options**\n113: \n114: - `NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n115: - `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n116: - `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` (deprecated alias to WithOptions)\n117: - Options: `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n118: \n119: ### Group interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`)\n120: \n121: ```go\n122: type Interface interface {\n123: \tV1alpha1() v1alpha1.Interface\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: `New(factory, namespace, tweakListOptions)` returns group accessor.\n128: \n129: ### Version interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`)\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: type Interface interface {\n133: \tAgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer\n134: \tCodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer\n135: }\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ### Per-type informers (`.../runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`)\n139: \n140: Example (`AgentRuntimeInformer`):\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n144: \tInformer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n145: \tLister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n146: }\n147: ```\n148: \n149: Also provides `NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, and analogous constructors for CodeInterpreter.\n150: \n151: ### Generic resource routing (`informers/externalversions/generic.go`)\n152: \n153: `ForResource` switches on:\n154: \n155: - `v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\")` → `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n156: - `...WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\")` → `...CodeInterpreters().Informer()`\n157: \n158: ### `internalinterfaces` (`informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`)\n159: \n160: ```go\n161: type NewInformerFunc func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n162: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n163: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n164: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n165: }\n166: type TweakListOptionsFunc func(*metav1.ListOptions)\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Listers (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n172: \n173: ### `AgentRuntimeLister` / `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` (`agentruntime.go`)\n174: \n175: ```go\n176: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n177: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n178: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n179: \tAgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n180: }\n181: \n182: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n183: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n184: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n185: \tAgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: `NewAgentRuntimeLister` uses `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()`.\n190: \n191: ### `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` (`codeinterpreter.go`)\n192: \n193: Same pattern for `CodeInterpreter`; `NewCodeInterpreterLister` uses `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`.\n194: \n195: ### Expansion (`expansion_generated.go`)\n196: \n197: Empty expansion interfaces for listers and namespace listers (all four types).\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## Fake clientset (`clientset/versioned/fake/`)\n202: \n203: | File | Role |\n204: |------|------|\n205: | `clientset_generated.go` | `NewSimpleClientset`, `NewClientset` — in-memory fake `Clientset` |\n206: | `register.go` | Scheme registration for fakes |\n207: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## File index (all paths under `client-go/`)\n212: \n213: | Path | Role |\n214: |------|------|\n215: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n216: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n217: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n218: | `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n219: | `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n220: | `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n221: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n222: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n223: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n224: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n225: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n226: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n227: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n228: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n229: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n230: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n231: | `informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n232: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n233: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n234: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n235: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n236: | `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Small factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n237: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n238: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n239: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n240: \n241: **Regeneration:** `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` (`k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch`, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`).\n\n(End of file - total 241 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# client-go library\n\nGenerated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n\n## Clientset\n\n### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n\tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n\tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n```\n\n### `Clientset` struct\n\nEmbeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n\n**Constructors**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/client-go.md","time":{"start":1775835751508,"end":1775835751513}}}}
